[normal]Written evidence from[bold] the Regulatory Policy Institute’s [bold]Better Government Programme[bold] (SCE0012)[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]Select committee effectiveness, resources and powers: Follow-up[bold]&#xa0;[bold]The Better Government Programme, a free-standing entity within the Regulatory Policy Institute, focuses on the machinery of government and regulation and on improvements to policy and regulatory processes. 
[normal]A
[normal] commission established by the Programme produced a series of recommendations on improving trust in institutions and processes. As part of its work, it considered the role and functions of Select Committees and this submission draws on that analysis
[normal], which was published as evidence to the Liaison Committee’s 2012 report
[normal]. 
[normal]This submission does not necessarily represent the corporate view of the RPI.
[normal]&#xa0;
